    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A researcher wants to compare the number of fires caused by fireworks to the number of fires caused by lightning.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">FireData.java</code>, complete the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">countMatching()</code> method. This method checks one <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Fire</code> object and returns 1 if the cause matches the parameter <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">cause</code> AND the name of the fire is longer than 6 characters. Otherwise, it returns 0.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">TheaterRunner.java</code>, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">drawResult()</code> method with the sum of calls to <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">countMatching()</code> on 5 fires.\r\n",
